From: Tauri Gobang Project <tauri-gobang@example.com>
Date: Fri, 28 Mar 2026 21:03:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Fix S_IWRITE undefined error on Android

Android NDK does not define S_IWRITE macro, only S_IWUSR.
This change adds a compatibility definition to map S_IWRITE to S_IWUSR.

This fixes the build error:
  "error: use of undeclared identifier 'S_IWRITE'" in zip.c.
---
 Rapfi/external/zip/src/zip.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Rapfi/external/zip/src/zip.c b/Rapfi/external/zip/src/zip.c
index 2073455..92784b9 100644
--- a/Rapfi/external/zip/src/zip.c
+++ b/Rapfi/external/zip/src/zip.c
@@ -13,6 +13,10 @@
 #include <sys/stat.h>
 #include <time.h>
 
+#ifndef S_IWRITE
+#define S_IWRITE S_IWUSR
+#endif
+
 #if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__WIN32__) || defined(_MSC_VER) ||              \
     defined(__MINGW32__)
 /* Win32, DOS, MSVC, MSVS */
